Sentencas: Cobalt-free SrFe1-xWxO3-delta (SFW, x = 0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3) perovskite cathode materials were synthesized by the citrate-EDTA-nitrate combustion method and systematically characterized in terms of their phase structure, thermal sintering and expansion behavior, conductivity and catalytic activity on oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: Properties characterization of tungsten doped strontium ferrites as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All SFW powders exhibit cubic perovskite structure and the good chemical compatibility between SFW cathode and Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) electrolyte is found.
Titulo: Properties characterization of tungsten doped strontium ferrites as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Introduction of W clearly inhibits the loss of lattice oxygen in temperature range of 400-900 degrees C and decreases the thermal expansion coefficients.
Titulo: Properties characterization of tungsten doped strontium ferrites as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As the W-doping concentration increases, the thermal sinterabilty weakens with decreasing grain size, and the conductivity decreases from 118.2 to 6.1 S cm(-1) at 600 degrees C. Among of SrFe1-xWxO3-delta-SDC composite cathodes, the SrFe0.8W0.2O3-delta-SDC cathode shows the smallest area specific resistance (ASR) value and the best ORR catalytic activity in range of 500-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Properties characterization of tungsten doped strontium ferrites as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode-supported single cell based on SDC electrolyte and SrFe0.8W0.2O3-delta-SDC composite cathode generates high power density and low polarization resistance.
Titulo: Properties characterization of tungsten doped strontium ferrites as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 700 degrees C, the peak density and polarization resistance are 694 mW cm(-2) and 0.036 Omega cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Properties characterization of tungsten doped strontium ferrites as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
